The paper deals with algorithms for computing the size of neighbourhoods in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and falls under the category of computational complexity. The use of the SETH and fpt-time algorithms suggests that the paper is likely to be in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
